.TH grommunio\-index 8 "" "grommunio" "grommunio admin reference"
.SH Name
grommunio\-index \(em Fulltext search index generator for grommunio mailboxes
.SH Synopsis
\fBgrommunio\-index\fP [\fB\-c\fP] [\fB\-e\fP \fIhost\fP] [\fB\-o\fP \fIfile\fP] [\fB\-p\fP \fIport\fP] [\fB\-qrv\fP] \fIuserpath\fP
.PP
\fBgrommunio\-index\fP \fB\-A\fP [\fB\-c\fP] [\fB\-p\fP \fIport\fP] [\fB\-qrv\fP]
.SH Description
grommunio\-index builds and maintains SQLite\-based fulltext search indexes for
grommunio mailboxes. It connects to the exmdb service to retrieve message
properties, extracts and sanitizes text from plain\-text and HTML bodies,
and writes the results into per\-user FTS5 databases.
.PP
In single\-user mode, the tool indexes the mailbox at the given
\fIuserpath\fP. In all\-user mode (\fB\-A\fP), it reads the user list from the
grommunio MySQL database and processes every user automatically, writing index
databases into a shared directory tree.
.PP
grommunio\-index is typically invoked via its companion systemd timer
(\fBgrommunio\-index.timer\fP) rather than manually.
.SH Options
.TP
\fB\-A\fP, \fB\-\-all\fP
Automatically process all local users. Cannot be combined with \fB\-e\fP,
\fB\-o\fP, or a positional \fIuserpath\fP argument.
.TP
\fB\-c\fP, \fB\-\-create\fP
Create a new index from scratch instead of updating an existing one.
.TP
\fB\-e\fP \fIhost\fP, \fB\-\-host\fP \fIhost\fP
Hostname of the exmdb server to connect to.
.br
Default: \fIlocalhost\fP (overridable via index.cfg)
.TP
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
Show a help message and exit.
.TP
\fB\-o\fP \fIfile\fP, \fB\-\-out\fP \fIfile\fP
Write the index database to a specific file or directory instead of the
default location inside the user's maildir.
.TP
\fB\-p\fP \fIport\fP, \fB\-\-port\fP \fIport\fP
Port of the exmdb server.
.br
Default: \fI5000\fP (overridable via index.cfg)
.TP
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
Reduce verbosity level. Can be specified multiple times.
.TP
\fB\-r\fP, \fB\-\-recheck\fP
Check all messages regardless of folder timestamps. Normally, folders whose
local\-commit\-time\-max has not changed since the last run are skipped.
.TP
\fB\-v\fP, \fB\-\-verbose\fP
Increase verbosity level. Can be specified multiple times.
.SH Configuration file
The optional configuration file \fB/etc/gromox/index.cfg\fP can be used to
override built\-in defaults. The file uses a simple key\-value format with one
directive per line. Lines starting with \fB#\fP are comments, and whitespace
around the \fB=\fP sign is ignored.
.PP
Command\-line arguments take precedence over configuration file values.
If the file is absent, all built\-in defaults apply and no error is raised.
.SS Configuration directives
.TP
\fBindex_root\fP
Root directory under which per\-user index databases are stored in all\-user
mode (\fB\-A\fP). Each user gets a subdirectory named after their login, with
\fBindex.sqlite3\fP inside it.
.br
Default: \fI/var/lib/grommunio\-web/sqlite\-index\fP
.TP
\fBuser\fP
System user to switch to when running as root. Only relevant in all\-user mode.
.br
Default: \fIgroindex\fP
.TP
\fBgroup\fP
System group to switch to when running as root. Only relevant in all\-user mode.
.br
Default: \fIgroweb\fP
.TP
\fBexmdb_host\fP
Default hostname of the exmdb server. Overridden by the \fB\-e\fP
command\-line option.
.br
Default: \fIlocalhost\fP
.TP
\fBexmdb_port\fP
Default port of the exmdb server. Overridden by the \fB\-p\fP command\-line
option.
.br
Default: \fI5000\fP
.SH Files
.TP
/etc/gromox/index.cfg
Optional configuration file for grommunio\-index.
.TP
/etc/gromox/mysql_adaptor.cfg
MySQL connection parameters, used in all\-user mode to retrieve the user list.
.SH See also
\fBgromox.cfg\fP(5)
